How to start a new python project with git (windows)

pre-requisites:
1. install git
2. install python
3. pip install virtualenv
makesure all paths (git,python) have been added to the system environment variables.

1. clone the repository
git clone repo-path

2. create a virtual env and activate it
cd project-name/
python -m virtualenv env-name
env-name\Scripts\activate

3. install packages
pip install "django<1.12" "selenium<4"

4. save your installed packages into requirements.txt
pip freeze > requirements.txt